eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The National Education, Health and Allied Workers' Union (Nehawu) has pledged its support for a complainant in a sexual assault case against a top Western Cape official. READ: Nehawu accuses CETA CEO of mismanagement The trial of provincial traffic chief Farrel Payne was set to start on Thursday but the matter has been postponed to Friday. Payne is facing charges related to sexual assault.